The paper proposes a new framework for interactive semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves designing a model-based intelligent agent, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), making cs.AI the second likely sub-category. The proposed framework involves maintaining state and generating natural language, which are also related to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses text-to-SQL datasets, which are related to database systems, making cs.DB a possible sub-category as well.
